organic_results.title: Domains of decision-making and school counselor use among high-school seniors
organic_results.snippet: Guidance programs, as emerging specializations, have received relatively little systematic, empirical sociological attention and are examined here in light of their allocative function and individual decision-making processes. High-school senior clients report counselors are consulted primarily for academic concerns, secondarily for vocational concerns, and hardly at all for adjustment concerns.
